Best part of chicken Parmesan? The thick layer of gooey, creamy cheese melted on top of crispy chicken. In this dish, we've recreated the same dreamy combination but given it a lighter twist by tossing in some greens. Needless to say, it's the best of both worlds.

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat the #oven{} to 450 degrees. In a shallow #dish{}, combine the @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, @parmesan cheese{1/4%cup}, @garlic powder{1%tsp}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Cut the @yukon gold potatoes{12%oz} into 3/4-inch cubes and toss on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp} and a large pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.

Place the potatoes in the oven for ~{25%minutes}, flipping once, until golden brown and tender.

Working one at a time, place the @chicken breasts{12%oz} between two pieces of #plastic wrap{}. Pound with a #rolling pin{}, #mallet{}, or heavy-bottomed pan until ½-inch thick. Season with @salt and @pepper.

Place the chicken on a lightly oiled baking sheet and spread with @sour cream{1%tbsp} each. Press the panko mixture into the sour cream. Place in the oven for ~{12-15%minutes}, until the chicken is cooked through and crispy.

Halve the @lemon{1}. Cut one of the halves into wedges. In a #large bowl{}, combine @sour cream{1%tbsp}, a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp}, a squeeze of lemon juice, and a pinch of @salt and @pepper.

When the potatoes are ready, toss them into the bowl with the dressing along with the @spinach{5%oz}. Season with @salt and @pepper.

Serve the crispy chicken Parmesan on a bed of spinach salad with a wedge of lemon for squeezing. Enjoy!